> I see it now. Page 50 of Bentley Engine and Clutch. Figure 15-9.

I just pulled one today and used a steering wheel puller. It worked
perfectly and only took a few seconds. I like this technique because
it pulls evenly on all three bolts at the same time, so no doing half
turns on each one to ease it off.

